text:
The repo is up to date. You'll see I added a lot in there, including blank templates for "profile", "fridge", and "create"(what "Brewery" links to). I also started a fragments file with a nav bar. I did not make a blank template for "register" which is what "Register here" links to--only because I forgot to.
Let me know if you have any questions! I couldn't really test the user authentication stuff, since we don't have any accounts made yet, but the whole thing should work with only a little modification.
Also, the dependencies for SQL may keep the app from running until you connect it to mySQL. The textbook info on doing so is here: <https://education.launchcode.org/java-web-dev-curriculum/intro-orm-mapping/reading/orm/index.html> everything is already set up on the intelliJ side of things, so you'll just need to set up the SQL side and make sure the db name, username and pw all match.

Also, the dependencies for SQL may keep the app from running until you connect it to mySQL. The textbook info on doing so is here:
everything is already set up on the intelliJ side of things, so you'll just need to set up the SQL side and make sure the db name, username and pw all match.
